main event: A civilian woman and her mother in Cushing, Wisconsin observed a brightly-colored disc-shaped object in the sky on March 1, 1967.
interesting points: The object was described as round, disc-shaped, and glowing with all colors.
The object appeared to be revolving and blinking lights.
A relative of the observers had seen a similar object the previous night at 0140Z on February 28.
The object was estimated to be much larger than a water tower would appear at 15 miles away.
The object hovered for about 25 minutes before fading into the horizon in a westerly direction.
